                  which was killed from the beginning of the world, meaning in figure. The Sacrifices of Abel, Noe, and Abraham, and al those of the people of Israel commaunded by the Lawe of Moses, figured and signified Christe. For whiche respecte chiefly, the lawe is reported of S. Paule, to haue the shadowe of the good thinges to come. S. Augustine writing against Faustus the Heretike, saieth: Testamenti Veteris Sacrificia omnia, multis &amp; varijs modis vnum Sacrificium, cuius nunc memoriā celebramus, significauerunt: All the Sacrifices of the olde Testament signified by manie, and sundrie waies this one Sacrifice, whose memorie we doo nowe celebrate. And in an other place he saieth,
                  
