               This much we confesse also, that onlesse the Sacrifice whereof we speake, were one and the same in substance of the thing offered, with the Sacrifice made vpon the Crosse, though the manner of offering be diuers: it were superfluous, and to God displeasant. For the newe Testament acknowledgeth, nor accepteth none other real and external Sacrifice, but the Sacrifice of the body and bloude of Christe, which hath succeded, as S. Augustine,
