the precise termes of Sacrificing Christe, or the Sonne of God vnto his Father, be not expressely set forth. The which termes, as to expresse them, it was not necessary, so of great discretion and wisedome, this holy learned Father, who liued in the Apostles time, eschewed: and yet he so signified the thing, by other wordes, as of the faithful it might be vnderstanded, and from the Infidels kept secret. Who if our Mysteries had bene with plaine speache made open vnto them, through lacke of faith, would haue had them in derision, and trodden them vnder their feete, as swyne doo precious stones, and as Heretiques doo at this day.
